  "title": "The effects of shocks in early life mortality on later life expectancy and mortality compression: A cohort analysis",
  "abstract": "I study how shocks in cohort-level early life conditions, as represented by deviations from trend in mortality before age 5, affect later mortality. I use data for six European countries and find that shocks that increase infant mortality decrease late",
